- `a2c3e93` — **latent crash fix**: `slice_transcript_ranges` now guards against inverted/empty evidence ranges (the model can emit `start>end`, which panicked the pipeline mid-replay). This was a real bug in the live capture pipeline, found via the router validation — worth it on its own.
 [...]      - `slice_transcript_ranges` (line ~484): CRASH FIX — added `|| start >= end` guard against inverted ranges (model emits start>end → panic `slice index starts at X but ends at Y`):
       ```rust
       let start = range.start.saturating_sub(1);
       let end = range.end.min(lines.len());
       if start >= lines.len() || start >= end { continue; }
       let segment = lines[start..end].join("\n");
       ```
